Certainly. Here is the simple way:

In your tailwind CSS file add it this way:

```markdown
/* ./src/styles/tailwind.css */

@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;

.myCustomClass {
  -ms-reveal: none;
}

@tailwind utilities;
```

Then in your `div` element apply `myCustomClass`.

```html
<div class="myCustomClass">
```

There you go! Now `-ms-reveal` style will be applied to that div along with any other TailWind classes you have added.

